                                                      News, Inc. Portland, Or. <br><br>
                                                      The author, James E. Parker, Jr mule@pinehurst.net,<br>
                                                      02/23/97:<br>
                                                      MULE is real-life report on CIA operatives<br>
                                                      The secret war in Laos was all-out mountian combat<br>
                                                      between main line North Vietnamese forces on the one<br>
                                                      hand &amp; rag-tag CIA mercenaries, Air America, Ravens, &amp;<br>
                                                      Hmong guerrillas on the other. CODENAME MULE<br>
                                                      describes the action in a straight forward, first-hand way.<br>
                                                      The CIA characters - Hog, Kayak, Bamboo, Clean, Digger,<br>
                                                      Greek, etc - most of whom are dead now, are clearly<br>
                                                      portrayed. If you want to know what it was really like to be<br>
                                                      trained by the CIA for more than a year and then sent<br>
                                                      upcountry Laos to fight a secret war with CIA operatives -<br>
                                                      read this book. Also read my second book, LAST MAN OUT,<br>
                                                      on CIA operations in Vietnam. <br><br>
